State files an Amended Information charging misdemeanor battery, contrary to Section 940.19(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.  No contest plea to the amended charge.   Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Have no contact with the victim, Brandon O. Martin;
3) Maintain full-time employment;
4) Pay restitution of $235.35 to Brandon O. Martin, 316 Riverview Drive, Apt. 6, Manitowoc, WI  54220;
5) Spend ten (10) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 01-15-16 at 8:00 a.m.;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Minutes.
